On Arms and Armour.
-------------------
 
First weapons.  Since combat here is done differently than anywhere else,
how weapons work also is done differently.  A level 1 player with the
most powerful non-magial weapon in the game will not do well here.
Each weapon has a range that is most effective for certain levels.
Low level player will do much better with lower power weapons than
they will with a weapon that was not designed for them.  Magical weapons
of course can bend this rule, but even then a magic weapon designed for
a high level player will not work well in the hands of a lower level
player.  This isn't to say that low level players only get wimpy weapons,
it just means that players can get powerful weapons comparable to their
level.  If you're looking for a MUD where a new player can get his hands
on the best weapon of the game and lay waste to everything, you wont find
it here.
 
Armour.  Armour here, from a player standpoint, does much the same thing
as it does on most other MUD's: It protects you from taking damage.
The more and better armour you can find the less damage you will take.
Keep in mind though that if your not very strong and you load yourself
down with a lot of heavy armour, while you may not take as much damage
in combat, you also will not be able to fight very well because of your
over encumbrance.
